                "A) The Cushing's reflex actively adjusted systemic heart rate to keep intracranial vascular volume static.",
                'B) Autoregulation maintained stable cerebral blood flow by adjusting intracranial vascular resistance within this blood pressure range.',
                'C) Cerebral perfusion pressure was kept constant by automatic fluctuations in cerebrospinal fluid production.',
